02:42.328 --> 02:45.024
Rome was the largest
and the most beautiful city

02:45.064 --> 02:47.532
of the ancient world.

02:47.567 --> 02:49.967
The magnificent facade
of the empire, however,

02:50.002 --> 02:53.403
could not conceal
the seeds of decay,

02:53.439 --> 02:57.273
the unhealthy dependence
of the economy on slaves,

02:57.310 --> 03:00.507
the disparity between
rich and poor.

03:00.546 --> 03:02.411
Behind the splendor
of the Forum

03:02.448 --> 03:05.508
were vast areas
of crowded slums.

03:05.551 --> 03:09.885
Escape from the slums was difficult
for there were few jobs available

03:09.922 --> 03:12.390
and practically none
for the unskilled.

03:12.425 --> 03:15.758
To keep idle citizens entertained
and out of mischief,

03:15.795 --> 03:19.856
frequent games and spectacles
were held at public expense.

03:19.899 --> 03:23.062
At first, only chariot races
were sponsored.

03:23.102 --> 03:24.899
But by the reign of Trajan,

03:24.937 --> 03:28.065
brutal combat to the death
had become popular.

03:28.107 --> 03:30.166
Earlier in Rome's history,

03:30.209 --> 03:33.076
elected representatives
exercised the power.

03:33.112 --> 03:35.512
But by now,
every function of government

03:35.548 --> 03:37.573
had been absorbed
by the emperor

03:37.617 --> 03:40.643
who was above the law
and ruled by decree.

03:40.686 --> 03:43.621
That a people as civilized
as the Romans,

03:43.656 --> 03:46.648
with the most humane
system of law ever devised,

03:46.692 --> 03:49.024
could tolerate the violation
of human beings

03:49.061 --> 03:50.995
is astonishing.

03:51.030 --> 03:53.794
This imbalance
and the irresponsible behavior

03:53.833 --> 03:56.859
of public officials
would become major reasons

03:56.903 --> 03:59.770
for Rome's eventual decline.

