and boarded up our house

06:49.609 --> 06:51.372
after they've evicted the person

06:51.410 --> 06:53.970
and threw their furniture
in the dumpster.

06:54.013 --> 06:56.038
So they're letting us know

06:56.082 --> 06:59.609
that they are stepping it up,

06:59.652 --> 07:01.984
boarding up somebody's house.

07:02.021 --> 07:04.080
This has been my family home.
This is my parents' house.

07:04.123 --> 07:06.353
I've lived here for 41 years.

07:08.961 --> 07:11.327
This is the only home
I've ever really lived in.

07:11.364 --> 07:14.162
This is the only-- this will always
be home to me, no matter what.

07:14.200 --> 07:15.929
- I'm a carpenter.
- There you go.

07:15.968 --> 07:18.095
Sandra, they're leaving.
Let them leave.

07:18.137 --> 07:20.662
- I'm a carpenter. So what?
- That's all I am.

07:23.175 --> 07:25.939
- Well, people pay their bills.
- This could happen to you.

07:25.978 --> 07:28.469
That's right.
So why do you think I'm doing it?

07:28.514 --> 07:30.641
I don't have to be happy about this,
but that's what I do.

07:30.683 --> 07:33.550
That's all I'm saying is that
maybe you can make another choice.

07:33.586 --> 07:36.180
- That's all we're saying.
- That's no reason for...

07:36.222 --> 07:37.780
You're a working-class person.

07:37.823 --> 07:40.849
people here to get upset
and almost get themselves hurt.

07:40.893 --> 07:43.623
We ain't gonna get hurt.

07:43.663 --> 07:45.187
Are you threatening us?

07:45.231 --> 07:48.029
Y'all gonna get on out of here.
You might end up even getting hurt.

07:48.067 --> 07:50.934
Talking about us getting hurt,
you might get hurt.

07:50.970 --> 07:53.097
There's gonna be
some kind of a rebellion

07:53.139 --> 07:56.165
between the people
that have nothing

07:56.208 --> 07:59.575
and the people that's got it all.

07:59.612 --> 08:01.136
I don't understand.

08:01.180 --> 08:03.080
There's no in-between no more.

08:03.115 --> 08:05.208
There's the people that's got it all

08:05.251 --> 08:07.151
and the people that have nothing.

08:10.022 --> 08:12.616
We gotta get this stuff
out of the house and packed up

08:12.658 --> 08:15.525
and be out of here
in about 30 days

08:15.561 --> 08:17.893
even though we don't
have a place to go.

08:24.403 --> 08:26.496
We designed this house.

08:26.539 --> 08:30.566
The property that it's on
was my family farm.

08:32.845 --> 08:37.839
So I've lost a piece
of my heritage with this.

08:37.883 --> 08:41.614
Why do you do this
to the hard-working people?

08:46.926 --> 08:50.293
Why do you take everything?

08:50.329 --> 08:53.196
You take everything
away from them.

08:53.232 --> 08:56.531
We're just middle-class,
hard-working people

08:56.569 --> 08:58.662
trying to make a living.

09:01.273 --> 09:04.140
Just trying to survive.

09:07.680 --> 09:09.773
An old Browning.

